    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="146"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/2896: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                        King of the Belgians</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leopold III</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-11">May 11,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have received Your Majesty’s telegram. As I stated in an address which I
                    delivered last night to representatives of the twenty-one American Republics,
                    the cruel invasion by force of arms of the independent nations of Belgium, The
                    Netherlands, and Luxembourg has shocked and angered the people of the United
                    States and, I feel sure, their neighbors in the Western Hemisphere. The people
                    of the United States hope, as do I, that policies which seek to dominate
                    peaceful and independent peoples through force and military aggression may be
                    arrested, and that the Government and people of Belgium may preserve their
                    integrity and their freedom. As an old personal friend I send you my warm
                    personal regards.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D. Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
